<div id="mattacloud" class="row-fluid mattalabs-container">
    <div>
        <div class="mattalabs-logo-container">
            <div class="mattalabs-logo"></div>
        </div>
        <h3 class="mattalabs-title">Mattacloud Plugin</h3>
        <hr>
        <h4>Hello Mattacloud user!</h4>
        <p class="description">
            To use this OctoPrint enabled printer with Mattacloud you need provide a valid authorization token.
            You can unlink this device from the Mattacloud at anytime by removing the token. You can also switch Mattacloud on and off using the toggle found on this plugin's tab.
        </p>
        <p class="description">
            Enter your authorization token in the box below. You can find your printer's token by logging in to your Mattacloud account. <a target="_blank" href="https://cloud.mattalabs.com/accounts/login/">Login</a>
        </p>
        <form>
            <div class="control-group">
                <label class="control-label">{{ _('Authorization Token') }}</label>
                <div class="controls">
                    <input id="settings_token_input" type="text" class="mattacloud-input-box d-inline-block" data-bind="value: auth_token">
                    <button id="settings_test_btn" class="btn btn-primary test-btn test-auth-token d-inline-block" type="button"><i id="settings_test_btn_spin" class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin" style="display: none;"></i>Activate</button>
                    <div class="small-text-div"><small>Paste your copied Mattacloud authorization token in here and click "Activate".<br>Don't have an account? Sign up to bring intelligence to your 3D printer. <a target="_blank" href="https://cloud.mattalabs.com/accounts/signup/">Sign Up</a></small></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="control-group">
                <label class="control-label">{{ _('Number of Cameras') }}</label>
                <div class="controls">
                    <select type="text" class="input-mini" id="num-cameras" data-bind="options: camera_numbers, optionsText: 'name', optionsValue: 'key', value: num_cameras">
                    </select>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div id="camera-1">
                <div class="mattacloud-inline-control-group">
                    <label class="control-label">{{ _('Primary Camera Snapshot URL') }}</label>
                    <div class="controls">
                        <input type="text" class="mattacloud-input-box" id="snapshot-url-1" data-bind="value: snapshot_url_1">
                        <div class="small-text-div"><small>We recommend an interval of around 30 seconds.<br>For real-time video use Mattacloud's stream functionality.</small></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="mattacloud-inline-control-group">
                <label class="control-label">{{ _('Interval') }}</label>
                <div class="controls input-append">
                    <input type="text" class="input-mini" id="camera-interval-1" data-bind="value: camera_interval_1">
                    <span class="add-on">sec</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            </div>
            <div id="camera-2">
                <div class="mattacloud-inline-control-group">
                    <label class="control-label">{{ _('Secondary Camera Snapshot URL') }}</label>
                    <div class="controls">
                        <input type="text" class="mattacloud-input-box" id="snapshot-url-2" data-bind="value: snapshot_url_2">
                        <div class="small-text-div"><small>The Mattacloud Beta does not work with a secondary camera.<br>Will be coming soon with future plans!</small></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="mattacloud-inline-control-group">
                    <label class="control-label">{{ _('Interval') }}</label>
                    <div class="controls input-append">
                        <input type="text" class="input-mini" id="camera-interval-2" data-bind="value: camera_interval_2">
                        <span class="add-on">sec</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>